title: Police: Missing 3-Year-Old Seaford Girl Found « CBS New York
text:
Police: Missing 3-Year-Old Seaford Girl Found February 6, 2017 8:36 AM 
SEAFORD, N.Y. (CBSNewYork) — Nassau County police say they’ve found a 3-year-old girl who was reported missing over the weekend. 
Nassau County police said Monroe Daba of Seaford was reported missing on Friday when her mother failed to appear with her for the father’s scheduled visitation, according to police. 
Police said her mother could be suffering from a mental disorder and may need medication. 
The little girl was found Sunday, but there’s no word on where she was located.
